parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the ABS light comes on
brake fluid leaks from the brake lines
and the vehicle may experience unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Failure and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering warning light comes on
the steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and there is a sudden loss of power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intermediate steering shaft can cause the steering wheel to vibrate, making it difficult to control the vehicle, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel vibrates
there is a clunking or grinding noise when turning
and the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearings can cause the vehicle to vibrate, making it difficult to control, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: There is a grinding or popping noise from the front wheels
the vehicle vibrates
and the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to become loose, making it difficult to control the vehicle, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose
there is a clunking or grinding noise when turning
and the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear air suspension can cause the vehicle to become unstable, making it difficult to control, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rear air suspension does not work
the vehicle sags or leans to one side
and there is a loss of ride comfort.
